 bject and may contain Ping Pong balls\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\, Puppetry\
 nThe Giant Space Monster That Ate Hamilton in 3-D" is a wild\, live-action
  human puppet experiment—part sci-fi spoof\, part theatrical chaos\, and
  entirely unpredictable. In this playful spectacle\, Smith & Reimer join f
 orces to save Hamilton (and the world) from a monstrous threat in a one-of
 -a-kind\, laugh-packed performance adventure that’s as heartfelt as it i
 s hilarious.\nGeneral Admission: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/t
 he-giant-space-monster-that-ate-hamilton-in-3-d/
