SUMMARY:Tacos & Extinction
LOCATION:The St. Luke's Mission\, 454 John St N (enter at Macauley St E)\, 
 Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Squirrel and Nut Productions (Hamilton\, ON)\nContent 
 warnings: Coarse Language\, Fog\, Simulated Stylized Death\nGenre: Theatre
 —Comedy\nIt's 1834 aboard the HMS Beagle. The menu is tacos. Sailing som
 ewhere between empire and paradise\, the Captain surveys\, Charles Darwin 
 devours\, and the Last Great Auk runs out of time. Never you mind the weav
 ing Spider\, bouncing Cricket\, or munching Gorilla. Tacos & Extinction is
  a surreal existential tragicomedy that blends the mythic\, historic\, and
  anthropomorphic into a vivid meditation on the Web of Life. Just one ques
 tion: is this boat sinking?\nGeneral Admission: $14\nMore info: https://hf
 tco.ca/events/tacos-extinction/
URL:https://hftco.ca/events/tacos-extinction/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
