SUMMARY:Medically Strange
LOCATION:Backroom @ Ringside\, 324 James St N (enter through alley at 12 Mu
 rray St E)\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Phoebe Taylor (Hamilton\, ON)\nSpecial: Relaxed Perfor
 mance\nContent warnings: Coarse Language\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\, Sketch
  Comedy/Improv\, Storytelling/Solo Show\nPhoebe has spent countless hours 
 in doctors waiting rooms\, specialists offices and "wellness" "clinics" as
 king “what is wrong with me.” Through stand-up and storytelling\, Medi
 cally Strange attempts to translate the experience of illness from the ins
 ide out. Phoebe’s dry humor and wit shares the ugly parts of being human
 —the snot\, the boogers\, the spit\, we stuff into our pockets\, the mom
 ents we’re too scared to look at ourselves. The ways we all feel strange
 .\nGeneral Admission: $8\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/medically-str
 ange/
