SUMMARY:No Die! – Or: How I Left Amsterdam and Almost Died in Africa
LOCATION:Mills Hardware\, 95 King St E\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Fedor Comedy (Amsterdam\, Netherlands)\nContent warnin
 gs: Coarse Language\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\, Storytelling/Solo Show\nAft
 er performing in 50 countries\, Dutch stand-up comedian Fedor Ikelaar shar
 es the story that nearly ended it. What starts as a naive trip to Sierra L
 eone spirals into motorbike chaos\, a car crash\, and a gunpoint encounter
  that isn’t even his closest brush with death. Blending sharp stand-up w
 ith vivid storytelling\, No Die! is a darkly funny true story about bad de
 cisions\, blind confidence\, and somehow surviving it all.\nGeneral Admiss
 ion: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/no-die-or-how-i-left-amsterda
 m-and-almost-died-in-africa/
