SUMMARY:LOVE & CRAÍC
LOCATION:The Staircase | Studio Theatre\, 27 Dundurn St N\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Squirrel Suit Productions (Hamilton\, ON)\nSpecial: Re
 laxed Performance\nContent warnings: Sexual Content\, Coarse Language\nGen
 re: Theatre—Comedy\, Storytelling/Solo Show\nStoryteller Carlyn Rhamey (
 The ADHD Project) takes you on a Celtic adventure like no other. Perilous 
 cliffs\, handsome rebels\, Viking ghosts\, and underpants gone rogue! This
  award-winning show (SAOR) returns\, bolder and wilder than ever. Lost in 
 Ireland. In love in Scotland. In trouble ...everywhere.\nGeneral Admission
 : $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/love-craic/
URL:https://hftco.ca/events/love-craic/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ae6e65443b089ac6c8f33083f772b102f2cc6c5a@hamilton-fringe-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260713T031033Z
DTSTART:20260719T000000Z
DTEND:20260719T010000Z
SUMMARY:The Last Hornblower
LOCATION:Centre For Talking Arts\, 154 James St S\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Live the Questions (Guelph\, ON)\nGenre: Storytelling/
 Solo Show\nDo not ask for whom the horn blows. Nobody on the Grande Torino
  did. The greatest soccer team Italy ever assembled simply rolled up their
  sleeves and confronted their opponents. Even the gods fought their demons
  when the horn bellowed from the deep at Ragnarok. We are never powerless.
  Never alone. Through the ageless art of storytelling\, we’ll sound the 
 horn that inspires us to step up when time is always against us.\nGeneral 
 Admission: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/the-last-hornblower/
URL:https://hftco.ca/events/the-last-hornblower/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
