 emes including descriptions of violence\nGenre: Theatre—Drama\, Musical/
 Concert/Opera\, Storytelling/Solo Show\nThrough an eerie combination of st
 ory and live music set in an otherworldly place\, a weathered cowboy lays 
 bare his haunted past\, straining against an encroaching hope in the darkn
 ess. Written\, directed\, and performed by the Gatineau-based Tony Martins
 \, OATS is an eerily ambient fusion of “western rock” music and tall c
 owboy tales. Acclaimed Hamilton-based guitarist Andrew Aldridge joins Mart
 ins on stage to help create a lush\, dark\, and atmospheric soundscape fro
 m two electric guitars in a musical conversation.\nGeneral Admission: $14\
 nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/the-outlaw-and-the-son/
