SUMMARY:Medically Strange
LOCATION:Backroom @ Ringside\, 324 James St N (enter through alley at 12 Mu
 rray St E)\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Phoebe Taylor (Hamilton\, ON)\nContent warnings: Coars
 e Language\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\, Sketch Comedy/Improv\, Storytelling/
 Solo Show\nPhoebe has spent countless hours in doctors waiting rooms\, spe
 cialists offices and "wellness" "clinics" asking “what is wrong with me.
 ” Through stand-up and storytelling\, Medically Strange attempts to tran
 slate the experience of illness from the inside out. Phoebe’s dry humor 
 and wit shares the ugly parts of being human—the snot\, the boogers\, th
 e spit\, we stuff into our pockets\, the moments we’re too scared to loo
 k at ourselves. The ways we all feel strange.\nGeneral Admission: $8\nMore
  info: https://hftco.ca/events/medically-strange/
URL:https://hftco.ca/events/medically-strange/
