 ngs: Coarse Language\, Violence\nGenre: Theatre—Drama\nWritten in iambic
  pentameter\, this play retells the myth of the young Icarus\, resigned to
  a life of monotony imprisoned inside the Labyrinth. Forever overshadowed 
 by the genius of his aging father\, Daedalus\, Icarus's world is thrown in
 to disarray when Helios\, the ancient sun god\, appears on the roof\, prom
 ising Icarus the two things he desires most- adoration and immortality. Wi
 nner of the 2026 New Play Contest at Hamilton Fringe Festival!\nGeneral Ad
 mission: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/icarus-is-falling/
